lobal-hope/refugee-and-migration-ministries", "city": null, "state": null, "summary": "UCC denominational program providing refugee and migration services through National Collaborative on Immigration. Works with grassroots organizing communities and Office of Public Policy & Advocacy in Washington D.C. Documented prayer letter and advocacy campaigns.", "fit_score": 7, "fit_reason": "Denominational ministry with established public advocacy platform, congregational giving networks, and documented prayer/advocacy materials", "source_query": "faith-based refugee resettlement agencies", "meta": {"import_source": "FINAL_CONSOLIDATED_ALL_WAVES.json"}}, {"org_name": "Upper Room Academy for Spiritual Formation", "org_type": "ministry", "website": "www.upperroom.org/academy", "city": null, "state": null, "summary": "Ministry of The Upper Room (General Board of Discipleship, United Methodist Church). Two-year intensive program since 1983 with 8 five-day sessions over two years. Ecumenical participants engage in daily prayer, silence, contemplative practices, study of Christian spirituality and theology.", "fit_score": 7, "fit_reason": "Established denominational formation program with long history, structured curriculum, published schedules, contemplative focus.", "source_query": "Upper Room Academy spiritual formation Methodist", "meta": {"import_source": "FINAL_CONSOLIDATED_ALL_WAVES.json"}}, {"org_name": "Urwego Bank Rwanda", "org_type": "ministry", "website": "urwegobank.com (assumed)", "city": null, "state": null, "summary": "Largest microfinance institution in Rwanda, serving 300,000+ clients (5% adult population). Founded 1997 by World Relief, merged with Opportunity Bank (2007), majority owned by HOPE International (99%). Mission: provide ladder of opportunity under Gospel.", "fit_score": 7, "fit_reason": "Operational Christian microfinance bank with explicit Gospel mission and demonstrated scale", "source_query": "Urwego Bank Rwanda Christian microfinance organization", "meta": {"import_source": "FINAL_CONSOLIDATED_ALL_WAVES.json"}}, {"org_name": "Veritas Forum", "org_type": "ministry", "website": "en.wikipedia.org/wiki/veritas_forum", "city": null, "state": null, "summary": "Founded 1992 (Harvard). Operates on 45+ campuses (Stanford, Yale, Brown, NYU, UVA). Creates forums exploring Christian relevance to philosophy, religion, science. 100+ community coordinators nationwide.", "fit_score": 7, "fit_reason": "Established campus ministry network with significant organizational infrastructure and demonstrated sustainable funding model", "source_query": "Veritas Forum Christian worldview university chaplaincy apologetics support", "meta": {"import_source": "FINAL_CONSOLIDATED_ALL_WAVES.json"}}, {"org_name": "Victim Offender Reconciliation Program (VORP) - Fresno", "org_type": "ministry", "website": "vorp.org", "city": null, "state": null, "summary": "Faith-based nonprofit established 1982 based on Biblical Vision of Shalom (Whole-Making Peace). Provides voluntary, non-fee mediation services to victims of juvenile crime and offenders. Encourages Christian churches in peacemaking, healing, restoration, forgiveness and reconciliation.", "fit_score": 7, "fit_reason": "Established Christian restorative justice program with 42+ year history, explicitly faith-based on Biblical principles, serves as model for other VORP programs", "source_query": "VORP victim offender reconciliation program Christian", "meta": {"import_source": "FINAL_CONSOLIDATED_ALL_WAVES.json"}}, {"org_name": "Victory Kids Christian Childcare", "org_type": "ministry", "website": "victorykidsministry.org", "city": "Denver", "state": "CO", "summary": "Multi-location Christian childcare network with emphasis on Bible-based early childhood education", "fit_score": 7, "fit_reason": "Director has visible online presence; organization has giving page and ministry support materials", "source_query": "Wave 2 Hunter Research", "meta": {"import_source": "FINAL_CONSOLIDATED_ALL_WAVES.json"}}, {"org_name": "Vision Films", "org_type": "ministry", "website": "visionfilms.net", "city": "Los Angeles", "state": "CA", "summary": "Independent Christian film distribution and production company. Leadership-led with documented supporter giving pages and faith community fundraising.", "fit_score": 7, "fit_reason": "Christian film production with public giving platforms and prayer letter updates", "source_query": "Hunter Research", "meta": {"import_source": "FINAL_CONSOLIDATED_ALL_WAVES.json"}}, {"org_name": "Visions Counseling", "org_type": "ministry", "website": "www.visionscounseling.org", "city": null, "state": null, "summary": "Established 2000 nonprofit 501(c)(3) offering affordable, solution-focused Christian counseling. Donations supplement session fees for those unable to pay full cost. Serves individuals, couples, and groups.", "fit_score": 7, "fit_reason": "Mature 501(c)(3) with established donation model supporting affordability. Over 20 years operational history demonstrates sustainability. Clear value proposition for donors.", "source_query": "Christian counseling network nonprofit 501c3 giving support mental health", "meta": {"import_source": "FINAL_CONSOLIDATED_ALL_WAVES.json"}}, {"org_name": "Whitefish Digital - Christian Founders Initiative", "org_type": "ministry", "website": "whitefishdigital.com", "city": "Seattle", "state": "WA", "summary": "Christian-led software agency mentoring faith-based startup founders and building tools for ministry organizations", "fit_score": 7, "fit_reason": "Active in Christian tech community with ministry focus; donation/partnership model for founder support", "source_query": "Wave 2 Hunter Research", "meta": {"import_source": "FINAL_CONSOLIDATED_ALL_WAVES.json"}}]'::jsonb)
  as x(org_name text, org_type text, website text, city text, state text,
       summary text, fit_score int, fit_reason text, source_query text, meta jsonb)),
-- Count how many existing rows (queue + pipeline) share each URL.
-- A URL on exactly one row is a person-specific page safe to dedup
-- against; a URL shared by many is a roster/platform page and must
-- NOT cause a skip, or we'd drop distinct people who list it.
existing_sites as (
  select site, count(*) as n from (
    select rtrim(lower(regexp_replace(website, '^https?://(www\.)?', '', 'i')), '/') as site
      from sales.scout_candidates where website is not null and btrim(website) <> ''
    union all
    select rtrim(lower(regexp_replace(website, '^https?://(www\.)?', '', 'i')), '/') as site
      from sales.leads where website is not null and btrim(website) <> ''
  ) w group by site)
insert into sales.scout_candidates
  (org_name, org_type, website, city, state, summary,
   fit_score, fit_reason, source_query, status, meta)
select s.org_name, s.org_type, s.website, s.city, s.state, s.summary,
       s.fit_score, s.fit_reason, s.source_query, 'pending', coalesce(s.meta, '{}'::jsonb)
from src s
where not exists (select 1 from sales.scout_candidates c
                  where lower(trim(c.org_name)) = lower(trim(s.org_name)))
  and not exists (select 1 from sales.leads l
                  where lower(trim(l.org_name)) = lower(trim(s.org_name)))
  and not exists (select 1 from existing_sites es
                  where s.website is not null and btrim(s.website) <> ''
                    and es.n = 1
                    and es.site = rtrim(lower(regexp_replace(s.website, '^https?://(www\.)?', '', 'i')), '/'));